flowchart TB
    accTitle: ZettelForge high-level architecture overview
    accDescr {
        ZettelForge is organized as a five-stage pipeline. Entry points are
        the MCP server and LangChain retriever, both of which call into the
        MemoryManager core API. The API dispatches writes through ingestion,
        entity processing, and background enrichment into the pluggable
        storage layer. Reads flow from the API through the retrieval
        pipeline and synthesis stage back to the caller. Storage is
        backed by SQLite by default with an optional LanceDB vector index.
        Infrastructure services (Ollama, fastembed, cache, retry) and
        observability (metrics, OCSF events, structured logs) support the
        pipeline. Optional extensions attach to the storage layer.
    }

    ENTRY["Entry Points<br>MCP Server · LangChain Retriever"]:::entry
    API["MemoryManager — Core API<br>remember · recall · synthesize"]:::api
    INGEST["Ingestion Pipeline<br>Validate · Build note · Extract facts · Update"]:::ingest
    ENTITY["Entity Processing<br>Index · Resolve aliases"]:::entity
    ENRICH["Background Enrichment<br>Causal · A-Mem evolution · HGAM"]:::enrich
    STORAGE["Storage Layer<br>SQLite default · LanceDB vector index"]:::storage
    RETRIEVE["Retrieval Pipeline<br>Intent · Vector + Graph · Rerank"]:::retrieve
    OUTPUT["Synthesis & Validation<br>RAG-as-Answer · Quality scoring"]:::output
    INFRA["Infrastructure<br>Ollama · fastembed · Cache · Retry"]:::infra
    OBSERVE["Observability<br>Metrics · OCSF events · Logs"]:::observe
    EXT["Extension Points<br>TypeDB · OpenCTI · OAuth/JWT · Sigma"]:::ext

    ENTRY --> API
    API -- "write" --> INGEST
    INGEST --> ENTITY
    ENTITY --> STORAGE
    INGEST -. "enqueue" .-> ENRICH
    ENRICH -. "updates" .-> STORAGE
    API -- "read" --> RETRIEVE
    STORAGE --> RETRIEVE
    RETRIEVE --> OUTPUT
    OUTPUT --> API
    INFRA -.- API
    OBSERVE -.- API
    EXT -.- STORAGE

